<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Glatius set up a straw man argument. He is using a series of lies to make his point. It is important not to be drawn into that and to question each mistake he makes.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I make mistakes, I'm human just like the next guy.  You're entitled to disagree with me and have your opinion of course.  However, calling me a liar is a bit extreme in as much as what we have are differing opinions.  You don't like what I have to say?  Okay, I don't fault you that.  But what I'm saying is not based on lies.<br>
<br>
People throw out the uber azure sleeves as an old world example of superior Monk armor, that rivaled Warrior armor.  How about the old world foreman's tunic?  The old 0 weight 10 AC tunic?  Wasn't that pretty uber?  Oh and those very heavy but high 5 ac kobold hide boots, weren't they pretty uber?  Really rivaled something like Ro's armor for paladins didn't it?<br>
<br>
Verant has come out and said publicly they made a mistake.  I'm agreeing with them, they made a mistake.  You want to convince them they were actually right when they have admitted they were wrong, more power to you.  Do that.  But the fact remains it was a growing problem.  And what exactly do you think will be dropping in PoP?  You figure the gear will actually be worse than Velious?   I don't.<br>
<br>
